HEADWORD: Ant-eater
<hw>Ant"-eat`er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of several species of edentates and monotremes that feed upon
ants. See <er>Ant-bear</er>, <er>Pangolin</er>, <er>Aard-vark</er>, and
<er>Echidna</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>antebellum</ent>⟦br⟧
